-----------------------------------------------------
-= Installing Voise res_speech module on Asterisk =-
-----------------------------------------------------

Voise connector for Asterisk Generic Speech Recognition API.
(http://www.asterisk.org/doxygen/1.4/AstSpeech.html)

In order to install 'res_speech_voise' module, you need to perform the following steps:

1 - Copy 'res_speech_voise.c' file to 'res' folder (ex: /usr/src/asterisk-12.8.2/res) of your asterisk sources.

2 - Edit the 'Makefile' ('res' folder) in order to add (before 'all:' label):

    2a - for Asterisk 1.4, 1.6 o 1.8: 

    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise
    
    2b - for Asterisk 11:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=110000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    2c - for Asterisk 12:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=120000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    2d - for Asterisk 13:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=130000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

3 - Run 'make install' (top of your asterisk sources)

4 - Check that you have the following lines in /etc/asterisk/modules.conf:

; Uncomment the following if you wish to use the Speech Recognition API
preload => res_speech.so
load => res_speech_voise.so

5 - Copy 'voise.conf' (configuration file) to:

/etc/asterisk